    Check if the agency is licensed. Each country features its own rules and laws regarding approving a private investigation agency, most of which are pertaining to the standard, skills and connection with its staff. Hence, to make sure that your case would get speedy and better results, be sure that the private investigator you've selected has the necessary licenses and approval from the authorities.

    Go for an experienced investigator. You may already know, experience counts a great deal with regards to providing better and faster results. To understand how to overcome a case and how to find out what the customer really wants to be found out discreetly requires tact and familiarity. A novice investigator might not be able to do this as easily as a professional.

    Check the technical facilities and equipments the agency has prior to hiring one. The days are gone of the detective moving around with magnifying lens. Today, technology as advanced a lot and science plays a crucial role in criminology and forensics. The way of communication has become technological, and therefore you'll need somebody that is technologically savvy to investigate your case.

    Discuss the price even before the investigation begins. Investigation is really a company that may go on and on and its duration is often uncertain. Also, the places in which the investigator has to go might vary based on the situation. Each one of these add to the expenses, and therefore you need to discuss each one of these and clarify all of the points before you hire an agency.